<br>
For those of you, who do not know me. I would like to introduce myself. <br>
I am RayPierre, lead to the Oracles of Fate. By now you all have a pretty good understanding of what went on that day.<br>
This atrocity has shamed me to no end. And I wish to extend my deepest most sincere apology to Kemidra for all of her pain on this matter.<br>
Rest assured that myself, and the high council of fate are taking full responsibility for the actions of my ex-probationary. And this wrong will be made right.<br>
I have been in contact with all the group members that were involved except for Draques who I apparently keep missing.. And Kharne and Kemidra have spoken with my Arch-Mage Aris. <br>
Although, there is no reasoning with one such as Joeler. And she feels she did nothing wrong. (Even though she has been avoiding me like the plague). Actions have been taken.<br>
And I just got word from her brother, that Joeler will not be adventuring in Norrath for a very long time. <br>
It seems she is having trouble finding a group now.<br>
Her other character Penasite however, is another story and I must get word out to everyone on that one. My high council and myself will be in touch with Kemidra in game to give an in character apology to her and make sure that proper restitution is made.<br>
The Oracles of Fate were forged in the fiery pits of honor and dignity. And I can only hope that with time and the actions of myself, and the high council that this blemish can be put behind us. <br>
It lightens my heart to see so many join together to help improve the quality of life on our server. And I look forward to the chance of meeting with the Champions of Marr under a much happier light. <br>
<br>
With honor and dignity may your sword hold true. <br>
And may the light speed you on your journey.<br>
<br>
RayPierre Ginzu<br>
Lead Oracle<br>
High Council Of Fate<br>
Ranger of the Surefall<br>
And rightful protector of all that just in the world<br>
